        Graduate education represents one of the most significant financial decisions a professional can make. The average cost of a master's degree ranges between $56,000 and $75,000 depending on institution type and program length, while doctoral programs can extend costs considerably further. Yet the funding mechanisms available to graduate students differ fundamentally from undergraduate financing—and understanding these differences is essential to making economically rational decisions about advanced education.
      </p>

