        Private student loans should be considered only after maximizing federal borrowing options. While private lenders occasionally advertise rates lower than federal loans, qualification for the lowest rates requires excellent credit (typically scores above 750) and often a creditworthy cosigner. Private loan rates generally range from 3% to 18% depending on creditworthiness, and lack federal protections including income-driven repayment plans, Public Service Loan Forgiveness eligibility, and extended forbearance options.
      </p>

